938527560.text: "HIF-1alpha, a component of HIF-1, can be induced by hypoxia or mutations of PTEN, VHL, succinate dehydrogenase (SDH), or fumarate hydratase (FH), as well as by the activation of ERBB2, SRC, endothelin-1 (ET-1), the RAS and MARK pathway, and the phosphoinositide 3-kinase (PI3K)-Akt-mTOR pathway."
